<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870206-0131 </DOCNO><HL> American Greetings Sells Unit</HL><DD> 02/06/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> AGREATENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> CLEVELAND  </DATELINE><TEXT>   American Greetings Corp. said it sold its Susy Card unit in West Germany to Herlitz Co., West Berlin, for cash. The amount wasn't disclosed.    The greeting-card concern said the sale would result in a pre-tax loss of about $12 million. But it said the loss would be offset by tax benefits of almost as much. </TEXT></DOC>